# MongoDB repository boundaries

## Repository responsibilities
- All MongoDB persistence lives in `packages/mongodb` (no ad-hoc drivers elsewhere).
- Every public repository method takes `orgId` explicitly where data is tenant-scoped.
- Return typed domain records (stable shapes for apps).

## Forbidden
- Calling OpenAI or any AI provider
- Reading/writing S3 objects
- HTTP calls (except Pinecone client used only from embedding helpers in this package)

## Tenancy enforcement
- Every query must filter by `orgId` for tenant-owned collections.
- Every document written must include `orgId` where applicable.
